{
    "name": "Giant Emperor Scorpion",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> warm deserts<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Ambush Pit (Ex)</b> A giant emperor scorpion can spend 1 minute digging itself into the soil or other ground debris. It then waits for its tremorsense to detect prey. When a creature comes within range, it can erupt from the ground as a free action as part of a charge, allowing it to use its pounce ability. When dug in, the scorpion has improved cover granting it a +10 bonus on Stealth checks.<br/><br/><b>Poison (Ex)</b> Sting\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 22; <i>frequency </i>1/round for 6 rounds; <i>effect </i>1d4 Str and 1d4 Dex; <i>cure </i>1 save. The save DC is Constitution-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A giant emperor scorpion is an ambush predator, burying itself in soil or sand until prey approaches."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This massive scorpion erupts from the sand, its giant pincers snapping and its tail stinger swaying threateningly.</i>",
